-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Oman Cement, United Development in Qatar
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-01-29T12:56:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-29/persian-gulf-stocks-oman-cement-united-development-in-qatar.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  slipped
0.3 percent to 1,401.56 at the 2 p.m. close in the emirate,
snapping a five-day rally. Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share
Index (SASEIDX)  advanced 0.2 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Oman Cement Co. (OCOI)   decreased the most since Nov. 30,
falling 2.1 percent to 0.421 rial. The sultanate’s second-
largest maker of the building material by market value said
full-year profit plunged 49 percent to 12.8 million rials ($33
million).  Saudi Cement Co. (SACCO)   surged to the highest since
July 2008, rallying 6.5 percent to 78 riyals. The Saudi
manufacturer of the building material said its board recommended
distributing a second-half dividend of 4.5 riyals a share.  United Development Co. (UDCD)   tumbled the most in almost
a month, decreasing 4.3 percent to 24.7 riyals. The Qatari
investor in infrastructure and energy said a potential stake
buyer pulled out after seeking to change the terms of an offer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
